Reasoning: The paper deals with the classification of large-scale scene datasets using deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges of increasing the depth of CNNs, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep supervision and residual learning to address convergence and overfitting issues is related to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the testing and comparison of the proposed models with other state-of-the-art networks involves performance evaluation (cs.MM).
